<TITLE> Govt to be fair with petitions to cancel cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com)The government will be fair in handling petitions for cancellation of political cases filed for persecution, including opposition leader Khaleda Zia's, the state minister for home said Tuesday . Decisions will be made on reviewing the nature of the cases, Tanjim Ahmed said replying to a question at his ministry. BNP Chairperson Khaleda Zia and her two sons on April 30 applied to the government for withdrawal of 20 cases filed against them. Of the 20 cases, four were filed against Khaleda, 11 against elder son Tarique Rahman and five against Arafat Rahman Coco, the younger one. BNP P Moudud Ahmed, Khaleda's younger brother Shamim Iskander and his wife, Tarique's wife Zobaida Rahman and her mother Syeda Iqbal Mand Banu, Coco's brothers-in-law Mostakim Reza and Mostakin Reza also filed applications. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina had earlier filed petitions for repeal of 10 cases against her. bdnew
